'''Abbosbek Saidzhon ugli Fayzullaev''' ({{langx|uz|Abbosbek Sayidjon oʻgʻli Fayzullayev}};<ref name="president.uz" /> born 3 October 2003) is an Uzbek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] or [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] and the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].

==Club career==
[[File:Fayzullaev, Arthur, Douglas Santos (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|Fayzullaev with [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]] in 2024|340x340px]]
On 6 May 2021, he made his debut in the [[Uzbekistan Super League]] against [[FC Turon|Turon]]. On 29 June 2022, he scored his first goal for [[Pakhtakor FC|Pakhtakor]] in a game against [[FC Bunyodkor|Bunyodkor]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/06/29/uzbekistan/pfl/pakhtakor-tashkent/football-club-bunyodkor/3751336/|title=Пахтакор VS. Бунёдкор 2:3|language=en|website=|date=2022-06-29|publisher=soccerway.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230104112044/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/06/29/uzbekistan/pfl/pakhtakor-tashkent/football-club-bunyodkor/3751336/|archive-date=2023-01-04|access-date=2023-07-28|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 4 August 2023, [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]] announced the signing of Fayzullaev to a three-year contract from Pakhtakor.<ref>{{cite web |title=Аббос Файзуллаев — с нами! |url=https://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/aboss-fayzullaev-s-nami/ |website=pfc-cska.com/ |publisher=PFC CSKA Moscow |access-date=4 August 2023 |language=Russian |date=4 August 2023 |archive-date=1 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240201103115/https://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/aboss-fayzullaev-s-nami/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 19, he made his debut for his new club in a match against Dynamo Moscow (1–2), coming on as a substitute in the 87th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/08/19/russia/premier-league/fk-dinamo-moskva/cska-moskva/4094260/|title=Dynamo Moscow VS. CSKA Moscow 2:1|language=en|website=|date=2023-08-19|publisher=soccerway.com|access-date=2024-07-02|archive-date=2023-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230729123733/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/08/19/russia/premier-league/fk-dinamo-moskva/cska-moskva/4094260/|url-status=live}}</ref> On September 24, he scored his first goal for CSKA in a 3:3 match against Rostov.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/09/24/russia/premier-league/fk-rostov-na-donu/cska-moskva/4094292/|title=Rostov VS. CSKA Moscow 3:3|language=en|website=|date=2023-09-24|publisher=soccerway.com|access-date=2024-07-02|archive-date=2023-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230907190018/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/09/24/russia/premier-league/fk-rostov-na-donu/cska-moskva/4094292/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was nominated for the [[IFFHS]] award for the Best Young Player of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/abbos-fayzullaev-nominirovan-na-zvanie-luchshego-molodogo-igroka-mira-v-2023-godu/|title=Аббос Файзуллаев номинирован на звание лучшего молодого игрока мира в 2023 году!|language=ru|website=pfc-cska.com|access-date=2024-08-04|archive-date=2024-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240201175941/https://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/abbos-fayzullaev-nominirovan-na-zvanie-luchshego-molodogo-igroka-mira-v-2023-godu/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 26 May 2024, Fayzullaev received the Breakthrough of the Season award in the [[2023–24 Russian Premier League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.championat.com/football/news-5566642-igrok-cska-fajzullaev-poluchil-premiyu-rpl-otkrytie-sezona.html|title=CSKA's Fayzullaev received the RPL "Breakthrough of the Season" award|language=ru|first=Aleksey|last=Yerin|website=www.championat.com|access-date=2024-10-30}}</ref>

On 29 October 2024, he was named the AFC Youth Player of the Year for 2023.<ref name="autoname1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/about_afc/afc_annual_awards/news/afc_youth_player_of_the_year_men_2023_abbosbek_fayzullaev.html|title=AFC Youth Player of the Year (Men) 2023: Abbosbek Fayzullaev|language=en|website=the-AFC|access-date=2024-10-30}}</ref>

On 30 July 2025, Fayzullaev signed a five-year contract with [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] in Turkey.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=İstanbul Başakşehir|url=https://x.com/ibfk2014/status/1950570994579517949|title=Hoş geldin Abbosbek Fayzullaev|trans-title=Welcome Abbosbek Fayzullaev|date=30 July 2025|access-date=30 July 2025|language=tr}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Fayzullaev Kasymov Fayziev.jpg|thumb|Abbosbek Fayzullaev, [[Mirjalol Kasymov]] and [[Davron Fayziev]]]]
[[File:Uzbekistan vs. Spain, 2024 Summer Olympic men's association football, 2024-07-24 (254).jpg|thumb|Abbosbek Fayzullaev scored goal. Uzbekistan vs. Spain, 2024 Summer Olympic men's association football, Parc des Princes (Paris).]]
Fayzullaev was called up to the Uzbekistan under-19 squad while still in the academy of Pakhtakor Tashkent.<ref name=FIFA>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/abbosbek-fayzullaev-the-rising-star-of-uzbekistan-football|title=Abbosbek Fayzullaev: The rising star of Uzbekistan football|first=Shilarze|last=Saha Roy|date=18 March 2023|accessdate=23 March 2023|website=fifa.com|archive-date=23 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323172642/https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/abbosbek-fayzullaev-the-rising-star-of-uzbekistan-football|url-status=live}}</ref> He was called up to the nation's under-23 squad in October 2021, for [[2022 AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualification]], and marked his debut with a goal against [[Bangladesh national under-23 football team|Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stats.the-afc.com/match_report/20935|title=Uzbekistan 6–0 Bangladesh|date=31 October 2021|accessdate=23 March 2023|website=stats.the-afc.com|archive-date=23 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323172647/https://stats.the-afc.com/match_report/20935|url-status=live}}</ref> For his performances at the [[2022 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]], in which Uzbekistan were beaten in the final by [[Saudi Arabia national under-23 football team|Saudi Arabia]], Fayzullaev won the Uzbekistan FA's Young Star of the Year award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ufa.uz/%F0%9F%8F%86-young-star-of-the-year-abbosbek-fayzullaev/?lang=en|title="Young Star of the Year" – Abbosbek Fayzullaev|date=26 November 2022|accessdate=23 March 2023|website=ufa.uz|archive-date=23 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323174611/http://ufa.uz/%F0%9F%8F%86-young-star-of-the-year-abbosbek-fayzullaev/?lang=en|url-status=live}}</ref>

He was called up to the under-20 side for the [[2023 AFC U-20 Asian Cup]], and went on to star in the competition. In the final against [[Iraq national under-20 football team|Iraq]], he won the penalty which sealed the 1–0 victory for his side, as teammate Umarali Rahmonaliyev converted from the spot, giving Uzbekistan their first ever Under-20 Asian Cup title.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.news.cn/20230319/7b9320a77a644650aa818406c5346c09/c.html|title=Uzbekistan beat Iraq to lift AFC U20 Asian Cup trophy|date=19 March 2023|accessdate=23 March 2023|website=english.news.cn}}</ref> For his performances, he was named the tournament's [[Most Valuable Player]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/national/afc_u20_asian_cup/news/fayzullaev_named_most_valuable_player.html|title=Fayzullaev named Most Valuable Player|date=18 March 2023|accessdate=23 March 2023|website=the-afc.com|archive-date=18 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230318220201/https://www.the-afc.com/en/national/afc_u20_asian_cup/news/fayzullaev_named_most_valuable_player.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 June 2023, he debuted for the [[Uzbekistan national football team|senior national team]] in a match against [[Oman national football team|Oman]], which ended in a 3–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liveresult.ru/football/matches/match1353236_Uzbekistan-Oman-online|title=Uzbekistan 3–0 Oman - 11 June 2023 - Live online broadcast of the football match.|language=ru|website=LiveResult|date=2023-03-28|access-date=2024-03-26|archive-date=2024-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240326164640/https://www.liveresult.ru/football/matches/match1353236_Uzbekistan-Oman-online|url-status=live}}</ref> On June 17, in a match against [[Tajikistan national football team|Tajikistan]], he scored his first goal for the national team, contributing to a 5–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liveresult.ru/football/matches/match1353247_Uzbekistan-Tajikistan-online|title=Uzbekistan 5–1 Tajikistan - 17 June 2023 - Live online broadcast of the football match.|language=ru|website=LiveResult|date=2023-06-14|access-date=2024-03-26|archive-date=2024-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240326164642/https://www.liveresult.ru/football/matches/match1353247_Uzbekistan-Tajikistan-online|url-status=live}}</ref> On 4 January 2024, he was included in the final squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]]. During the tournament, he played in five matches and scored two goals, against the [[India national football team|India]] and [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]] teams.

In 2024, he participated in the [[2024 Summer Olympics]] in [[Paris]] as part of Uzbekistan's Olympic football team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/paris-2024-olympics-squads-mens-football-roster/blt226bcc0e96f06039|title=Olympics 2024 squads: USMNT, Spain, France & every official men's football tournament roster {{!}} Goal.com|language=en|website=|date=2024-07-24|publisher=Goal.com|access-date=2024-07-24|archive-date=2024-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240724170247/https://www.goal.com/en/lists/paris-2024-olympics-squads-mens-football-roster/blt226bcc0e96f06039|url-status=live}}</ref> He played in the match against the [[Spain Olympic football team|Spain]].

On 14 November 2024, during a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2026 World Cup qualification]] match against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]], he scored a brace, marking his first double for the national team in a match that ended 3–2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports.ru/football/1116535467-fajzullaev-sdelal-dubl-v-matche-otbora-chm-2026-s-katarom-uzbekistan-p.html|title=Fayzullaev scored a brace in the 2026 World Cup qualifier against Qatar. Uzbekistan lost after conceding the decisive goal in the 12th added minute|language=ru|website=www.sports.ru|access-date=2024-11-22}}</ref>

